        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Personally, I see nothing wrong with other people approaching necro-levels of mana regen. Sure, it'd be great if we got more, but it would probably end up hurting the class more than it already is. Why?</P><P>Balance.</P><P>First of all, we are already far better at soloing than most other classes. Increasing our mana regen by allowing KEI to stack would probably increase our kill rate by 75% at least. Do we really need that? Don't you think that would be just a wee bit too much?</P><P>Secondly, why do you think they've improved other classes mana regen? Balance. It's really difficult to balance a game when you have such large disparate rates of mana regen that were present before Luclin, especially when only 2 (of 7) classes were on the high end of the spectrum. By bringing the mana regen of the other classes closer to a necro's, they have essentially brought balance to one aspect of the game *without nerfing anyone*, ie not only did our mana regen rate not go down, it went UP!</P><P>While our mana regen is no longer light years ahead of everyone else's, we are still ahead (I consider needing to Cannibalise every tick to be a huge inconvenience no matter how fast the mana regen rate). This has similarities to the balancing of melee damage. They've simply increased the base point for comparison of mana regen. Apart from chanters and shammies, the other caster classes still don't have decent rates of mana regen on their own.</P><P>Tenaiya Soulscorcher<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
